event: The key following key(s) were pressed: ['Control_L', 'Escape'].
description: The user pressed the **Control** and **Escape** keys simultaneously.  As a result, the **Start Menu** expanded.
outcome: The Start Menu expanded to reveal program shortcuts and system options, with the cursor hovering over the "Control Panel" option.

event: The key following key(s) were pressed: ['Alt_L', 'c'].
description: The user pressed the key combination 'Alt_L' + 'c', which brought the "Control Panel" window into focus.

event: The key following key(s) were pressed: ['Control_L', 'Escape'].
description: The user pressed the  **Control** and **Escape** keys simultaneously. This action opened the Windows XP Start Menu.
outcome: The Windows XP Start Menu opened on the left side of the screen.

event: The key following key(s) were pressed: ['c'].
description: The user pressed the 'c' key, highlighting the "Control Panel" option in the Start Menu.
outcome: The "Control Panel" option in the Start Menu became highlighted.

event: The key following key(s) were pressed: ['Right'].
description: The user pressed the right arrow key.

event: The key following key(s) were pressed: ['Right'].
description: The user pressed the right arrow key, which highlighted the "Control Panel" item on the Windows taskbar.
outcome: The "Control Panel" item on the Windows taskbar became highlighted.

event: The key following key(s) were pressed: ['p', 'o'].
description: The user typed the shortcut keys 'p' then 'o'. This action de-selected "Add or Remove Programs" and brought the mouse focus to the "Power Options" icon.
outcome: The "Add or Remove Programs" icon is no longer highlighted and its tooltip has disappeared. The mouse cursor has become visible near the "Power Options" icon.

event: The key following key(s) were pressed: ['Return'].
description: The user pressed the **Enter** key while the "Power Options" icon in the Control Panel was selected, opening the "Power Options Properties" window.
outcome: A new window titled "Power Options Properties" opened in front of the Control Panel.

description: The user clicked the "Turn off monitor" dropdown menu.
outcome: The "Turn off monitor" dropdown menu expanded.

description: The user clicked the mouse, selecting "Never" from the "Turn off monitor" dropdown menu within the "Home/Office Desk" power scheme.
outcome: The "Turn off monitor" dropdown menu closed. The selected option within the menu is "Never".

description: The user clicked the "OK" button in the "Power Options Properties" window. As a result, the "Turn off monitor" setting for the "Home/Office Desk" power scheme was changed to "Never".
The user clicked on the "Display" icon within the Control Panel, resulting in the "Display Properties" window opening.
outcome: The "Control Panel" window is replaced by the "Display Properties" window.

event: The mouse clicked on DesktopScreen SaverAppearanceSettings.
description: The user clicked the "Appearance" tab within the "Display Properties" window.
outcome: The "Appearance" tab of the "Display Properties" window is displayed.

description: The user clicked the mouse on the "Screen saver" dropdown menu. As a result, the menu expanded.
The user clicked the mouse, selecting "None" from the "Screen Saver" dropdown menu.
outcome: The screen saver selection dropdown menu closed, "None" is now the selected option.

description: The user clicked the highlighted "OK" button in the "Display Properties" window.
